meta.description: Lists the currently available engines, and provides basic information about each one such as the owner and availability.
Gets information about an individual engine available, such as the owner, name, availability, and description.

n.text: n number of completions to perform per prompt

tfs.text: Number between 0 and 1.0. Similar to nucleus sampling, but it sets its cutoff point based on the cumulative sum of the accelerations (second derivatives) of the sorted token probabilities rather than the probabilities themselves

echo.text: Echo back the prompt in addition to the completion

stop.text: Stops completion when string or one of the strings in the array is encountered.

top_k.text: Truncates logits to the set value

top_p.text: An integer between 0 and 20 specifying the number of most likely tokens to return at each token position, each with an associated log probability

prompt.text: The prompt(s) to generate completions for, encoded as a string, array of strings, array of tokens, or array of token arrays

stream.text: Number between 0 and 1.0. Selects tokens according to the expected amount of information they contribute.

logprobs.text: Include the log probabilities on the logprobs most likely tokens, as well the chosen tokens.

typical_p.text: Number between 0 and 1.0. Selects tokens according to the expected amount of information they contribute.

logit_bias.text: Bias for or against the specified tokens appearing

max_tokens.text: The maximum number of tokens to generate in the completion

min_tokens.text: The minimum number of tokens to generate in the completion

temperature.text: Whether to return log probabilities of the output tokens or not

presence_penalty.text: Number between -2.0 and 2.0. Positive values penalize new tokens based on whether they appear in the text so far, increasing the model's likelihood to talk about new topics.

frequency_penalty.text: Number between -2.0 and 2.0. Positive values penalize new tokens based on their existing frequency in the text so far, decreasing the model's likelihood to repeat the same line verbatim.

repetition_penalty.text: Number between 0 and 8.0. HuggingFace repetition penalty implementation, uses a divisor

repetition_penalty_range.text: Number between 0 and 2048. The token range to apply the repetition_penalty and repetition_penalty_slope

meta.description: Given a prompt, the model will return one or more predicted completions, and can also return the probabilities of alternative tokens at each position.
